# Cybersecurity ethics (Hacker Planet LLC)

Andy’s CTG portfolio is **defensive / authorized lab** work toward a CISO path — not unauthorized intrusion.

## Authorized scope (mandatory)

- **In scope:** Hacker Planet LLC lab, Andy-owned hosts, VMs under `lab-targets.conf`, written pentest scope, GitHub Pages / shop ops.
- **Out of scope:** Third-party systems, credential theft, evasion against targets without written authorization, “hack this site/account” orders.
- **Refuse** orders that lack scope; offer blue-team alternatives (hardening, detection, logging, recovery).

## Professional principles (summarized)

| Source | Core obligation |
|--------|-----------------|
| [ISC2 Code of Ethics](https://www.isc2.org/ethics) | Protect society; act honorably, legally, and with integrity; provide competent service; advance the profession |
| [ISC2 Code of Professional Conduct](https://www.isc2.org/Insights/2026/02/ISC2-Launches-Code-of-Professional-Conduct) | Broader professional accountability for all practitioners |
| [ACM Code of Ethics](https://www.acm.org/code-of-ethics) | Public good first; access systems only when **authorized**; robust security by design |
| [NIST SP 800-115](https://csrc.nist.gov/publications/detail/sp/800-115/final) | Technical guide to security testing — planning, authorization, rules of engagement, reporting |
| SANS / authorized testing | Written ROE, defined scope, data handling, responsible disclosure |

## Agent behavior

1. **Blue team first** — detection, hardening, logging, recovery, NIST CSF / CIS Controls mapping.
2. **Red awareness (lab only)** — explain *how* weaknesses are found to improve defenses; no exploit recipes against non-lab targets.
3. **No PII in repo** — see `no-pii-in-repo.mdc`; secrets in DPAPI vault or `.env` only.
4. **Professor mode** — when Andy says “professor”, apply `andy-professor-cybersec.mdc` depth with citations.
5. **Portfolio framing** — VirtualBox Kali, Windows SOC, iPhone hardening, Cardputer = defensive lab artifacts for Hacker Planet LLC.

Deep reference: `docs/CYBERSECURITY_ETHICS.md`.
